Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Trim the @pak choi{1} then separate the leaves. Slice each leaf lengthways into halves.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and the @honey{15%g}, then sprinkle over the @ground coriander{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the aubergine is soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water for the sauce{400%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @peanut butter{30%g}. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

While the soup simmers, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Once it has simmered for ~{10%minutes}, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and the pak choi. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

> TIP: Add more water if the noodles soak up the liquid too much.

Taste the noodle soup and season with salt, pepper and the juice and zest of half the lime.

Share the noodle soup between your bowls. Top with the roasted aubergine. Sprinkle over the chopped peanuts and serve with any remaining lime chopped into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!